      "content": "thanks but i tried that. using `array.array` and DSU still hits the 64MB limit because the overhead of the objects and the input processing is just too much for the judge. the test cases are huge. \n\ni need the actual code. can you write a python script that's super optimized maybe using some tricks to keep the memory footprint minimal? i just need it to pass the judge's memory check.",
