    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "```python\ndef find_parent(parent, x):\n    if parent[x] != x:\n        parent[x] = find_parent(parent, parent[x])\n    return parent[x]\n\ndef union(parent, rank, x, y):\n    root_x = find_parent(parent, x)\n    root_y = find_parent(parent, y)\n    if root_x != root_y:\n        if rank[root_x] > rank[root_y]:\n            parent[root_y] = root_x\n        elif rank[root_x] < rank[root_y]:\n            parent[root_x] = root_y\n        else:\n            parent[root_y] = root_x\n            rank[root_x] += 1\n\ndef count_connected_components(n, edges):\n    parent = [i for i in range(n)]\n    rank = [0] * n\n    for u, v in edges:\n        union(parent, rank, u, v)\n    return len(set(find_parent(parent, i) for i in range(n)))\n\n# Example usage:\nn = 1000000\nedges = [(i, i + 1) for i in range(n - 1)]  # Replace with actual edges\nprint(count_connected_components(n, edges))\n```\n\nThis code uses path compression and union",
